# Release & CI

## Agent guardrails

- **Do not** bump `packages/model-viewer/package.json` version unless explicitly asked
- **Do not** create or push git tags unless explicitly asked

## Human pre-flight

1. Changes merged to the release branch
2. Confirm `packages/model-viewer/package.json` version is the intended release
3. Commit version bump if not already on the branch

## Release (`@london-dynamics/model-viewer` only)

Tag must match `package.json` exactly (`v4.7.3` ↔ `"version": "4.7.3"`).

```bash
git tag v4.7.3
git push origin v4.7.3
```

Or **workflow_dispatch** in Actions — select the **tag ref** (e.g. `v4.7.3`), not a branch.

**Strict semver only** — `vX.Y.Z` triggers release. Pre-release tags (e.g. `v4.2.0-beta.49`) do **not**.

## `release-package.yml` (on tag push)

| Step | Action |
|---|---|
| Validate | Tag version equals `package.json` |
| Install | `npm ci` (`LONDON_DYNAMICS_NPM_AUTH_TOKEN`) |
| Build | `npm run build --workspace=packages/model-viewer` |
| Publish | `npm publish --ignore-scripts` → GitHub Packages |
| Release | GitHub Release with auto-generated notes |

**Note:** CI uses `--ignore-scripts` so publish does not re-run `prepublishOnly` / `prepare` (build already ran). Local `npm publish` still runs the full build. Workflow does **not** run tests before publish. Re-publishing the same version fails at the registry.

## Docs deploy (separate from npm release)

[`deploy-documentation.yml`](../../.github/workflows/deploy-documentation.yml):

- Triggers on **push to `master`** or manual dispatch
- `npm run build` → `ci-before-deploy.sh` → GitHub Pages (`gh-pages`)
- Independent of npm tags — docs and package releases can ship separately

## One-time admin (repo settings)

- Actions → Workflow permissions → **Read and write**
- Optional: tag protection for `v*`
